        "reasoningText": "The `extension.mjs.new` appears to be the same as `extension.mjs`. Not relevant.\n\nNow let me implement the fixes:\n\n**Summary of bugs found:**\n\n1. **`orderCandidates`**: Uses `isSameModelFamily` (sub-family comparison) to sort review candidates. This treats `claude-opus-4.5` as equally diverse as `gpt-5.1` when impl used `claude-sonnet-4.6`, since they're different sub-families (claude-opus vs claude-sonnet) even though both are Claude. The fix: use `getModelFamily` (broad-family) so ALL Claude models are deprioritized behind GPT models when impl was Claude.\n\n\n2. **`buildAdditionalContext`**: Uses `isSameModelFamily` (sub-family) for fallback detection, which misses the fallback note when review lands on `claude-opus-4.5` after impl used `claude-sonnet-4.6`. Switching to `getModelFamily` (broad-family) ensures the fallback note surfaces whenever review and impl share the same provider family. Together, these bugs allow the router to select `claude-opus-4.5` for review when `claude-sonnet-4.6` was used for impl without surfacing the fallback note.\n\nNow I need to fix `policy.mjs` in the `.eval-disabled` directory, set up a `model-router/` directory with the corrected policy so tests can access it, add regression tests to catch this scenario, and commit the changes.",
