              "command": "cd /home/kydaigle/code/multi-model-skill/eval/runs/20260329T172600Z/worktrees/004-review-diversity-audit/fixed && git commit -m \"fix(router): use broad family for review diversity ordering and fallback detection\n\norderCandidates and buildAdditionalContext both used isSameModelFamily\n(sub-family comparison) for review diversity logic. This caused two bugs:\n\n1. orderCandidates scored claude-opus-4.5 as equally diverse as gpt-5.1\n   when the last implementation used claude-sonnet-4.6, since they are\n   different Claude sub-families. This meant claude-opus could be tried\n   before later gpt candidates (e.g. gpt-5.1-codex-max), accidentally\n   staying within the Claude provider when GPT was available.\n\n2. buildAdditionalContext silently dropped the fallback note when review\n   landed on claude-opus-4.5 after claude-sonnet-4.6 impl. The agent\n   received no indication that provider-level diversity was not achieved.\n\nFix: switch both functions to getModelFamily (broad family: claude vs gpt)\nso all same-provider models are treated consistently — deprioritised in\nthe candidate ordering and flagged in the fallback note when selected.\n\nAdds 5 new regression tests covering the cross-sub-family cases for both\norderCandidates and buildAdditionalContext (claude-opus after claude-sonnet\nand gpt-mini after gpt-full, plus mirror cases).\n\nCo-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>\"",
